race.description: Tgs2go Traffic Control Mdn Showcase Plate
race.comment: LAMBERTINA (9) had been well educated before winning comfortably at Gosford on debut. He again raced forward at Canterbury following that but lacked a kick at the business end. He will be better for that outing and is suited in country grade. Collett's booking suggests she's pleasing. VALIANT DREAMER (12) is also Sydney-trained and presents on debut. She just missed in a recent Warwick Farm trial and the in-form Boudvillain takes the ride. This looks suitable and she can feature with average luck from an awkward gate. MILITANT (2) was well supported at Newcastle on debut but didn't finish it off after stalking the lead. The longer sprint suits, and she has the blinkers applied for the first time. Improvement is likely, and she goes into the mix on an each-way basis. FAN SEA DIVA (7) can fire a shot on debut.
